# TECHNICAL REQUIREMENTS DOCUMENT (TRD)

## 1. Document Overview

### 1.1 Purpose
This Technical Requirements Document (TRD) translates the Functional Requirements Document (FRD) into detailed technical specifications for implementing an AWS Glue-based data processing pipeline. This document provides implementation-ready technical design for data ingestion, cleaning, cataloging, SCD Type 2 implementation using Apache Hudi, and aggregation processing. The TRD serves as the authoritative source for AWS Glue job development and code generation.

### 1.2 Scope
This TRD covers the following technical implementation areas:
- AWS Glue job specifications for reading CSV data from S3
- PySpark-based data cleaning and deduplication transformations
- AWS Glue Data Catalog table registration and schema definitions
- Apache Hudi integration for SCD Type 2 implementation with metadata tracking
- Incremental processing logic and change detection mechanisms
- Aggregation logic for customer spend calculation
- Error handling, validation, and monitoring strategies
- Runtime parameters and execution configurations

