### **TR-CLEAN-001: Implement Null Value Removal for Customer Dataset**
- **FR Reference**: FR-CLEAN-001
- **Objective**: Remove records containing string "Null" (case-sensitive) or NULL values from customer dataset
- **Source Details**: 
  - Source: In-memory customer DynamicFrame from TR-INGEST-001
  - Schema: CustId, Name, EmailId, Region
- **Target Details**: Cleaned in-memory DynamicFrame/DataFrame
- **Schema**: Same as source (CustId, Name, EmailId, Region)
- **Transformation Logic**:
  - Convert DynamicFrame to DataFrame for filtering operations
  - Apply filter to remove records where any column contains:
    - String literal "Null" (case-sensitive match)
    - NULL/None values
  - Filter condition: `(col("CustId") != "Null") & (col("CustId").isNotNull()) & (col("Name") != "Null") & (col("Name").isNotNull()) & (col("EmailId") != "Null") & (col("EmailId").isNotNull()) & (col("Region") != "Null") & (col("Region").isNotNull())`
  - Convert back to DynamicFrame if needed for Glue operations
- **Validation Rules**:
  - Verify no records contain string "Null" in any field after filtering
  - Verify no records contain NULL values in any field after filtering
  - Log count of records removed
  - Validate at least one record remains after filtering (or handle empty dataset scenario)
- **Error Handling**:
  - If all records filtered out: Log warning, continue processing with empty dataset or fail based on business rule (not specified in FRD)
  - If filtering operation fails: Log error, raise exception, fail job
- **Runtime Parameters**:
  - `--null_string_value`: "Null" (default, case-sensitive)
- **Operational Notes**:
  - Execute immediately after TR-INGEST-001
  - Log before and after record counts
  - Emit CloudWatch metric for records removed

